'''Murad Meneshian''' is a research chemist, journalist, translator, and researcher.<ref name=mazda>{{cite book|last=Hovannisian|first=ed. by Richard G.|title=Armenian Sebastia/Sivas and Lesser Armenia|year=2004|publisher=Mazda Publ.|location=Costa Mesa, Calif.|isbn=1568591527}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Raffi, The Prophet From Payajuk By Murad A. Meneshian|url=http://www.keghart.com/Apelian-Raffi|publisher=Keghart|accessdate=20 February 2013}}</ref>
Of [[Armenians|Armenian]] descent, Meneshian is a research chemist who has worked for Abbott Laboratories, Zenith corporation, and Bell Laboratories at AT&T/Lucent technologies, where he received a patent. His articles have been published in the ''Proceedings of the Third International Symposium on Very Large Scale Integration Science and Technology''.<ref name=mazda/> He has engaged in many studies of [[Armenia]] and [[Mesopotamia]].<ref name=mazda /> He has translated from Armenian to English Vaham Hampartsumian's Guighashkharh and is engaged in a study of the life and works of famed Armenian writer [[Raffi (novelist)|Raffi]]. For many years he has been a regular contributor to the ''Armenian Weekly''.
His book ''Raffi: the prophet from Payajuk'' has been awarded Book of the Week by the Armenian Weekly.<ref>{{cite news|last=Barsoumian|first=Nanore|title=Book of the Week: ‘Raffi: The Prophet From Payajuk’|url=http://www.armenianweekly.com/2010/10/29/book-of-the-week-%E2%80%98raffi-the-prophet-from-payajuk%E2%80%99/|accessdate=20 February 2013|newspaper=Armenian Weekly|date=October 29, 2010}}</ref>
