{{Multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=January 2013}} {{BLP primary sources|date=January 2013}} {{Notability|Academics|date=January 2013}} {{Like resume|date=January 2013}} }} {{Infobox person | name = Yasuhiro Matsuda | image =松田康博20140918.jpg | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date|1965|11||}} | birth_place = {{JPN}} [[Hokkaido]] | death_date = | death_place = | restingplace = | othername = 松田 康博 | occupation = international politic | yearsactive = | spouse = | children = }}
{{nihongo|'''Yasuhiro Matsuda'''|松田 康博|Matsuda Yasuhiro|born November, 1965 in [[Hokkaido]]}} is a Japanese [[professor]] of international politics at the [[University of Tokyo]].
== Biography == Matsuda received his Ph.D. in law from Graduate School of Law at Keio University in Tokyo. He spent sixteen years in the National Institute for Defense Studies (NIDS), Japan Defense Agency (later, Ministry of Defense), as an assistant and a senior research fellow. He moved to the Institute of Oriental Culture of the University of Tokyo in 2008. He is specializing in political and diplomatic history of Asia, politics and foreign relations in the PRC and Taiwan, the Cross-Strait Relations, and Japan's foreign and security policies. He was a member of the Council on Security and Defense Capability in the New Era, the advisory group of the Prime Minister in 2010.<ref>{{citation|title=Japan’s Visions for Future Security and Defense Capabilities in the New Era: Toward a Peace‐Creating Nation|url=http://www.kantei.go.jp/jp/singi/shin-ampobouei2010/houkokusyo_e.pdf}}.</ref> He is the winner of the seventh Yasuhiro Nakasone Award of Excellence in 2011.<ref>{{citation|title=Recipients of the Seventh Nakasone Yasuhiro Award|url=http://www.iips.org/nya/nya7re.pdf}}.</ref> He has published numerous books and articles in Japanese and English. His recent publication in English is “Taiwan in the China-Japan-US Triangle,” Gerald Curtis, Ryosei Kokubun, and Wang Jisi eds., Getting the Triangle Straight: Managing China-Japan-US Relations, New York: Japan Center for International Exchange, 2010.<ref>{{citation|title=Profile and Academic CV of Yasuhiro Matsuda’s official website|url=http://www.ioc.u-tokyo.ac.jp/~ymatsuda/en/biog.html}}.</ref>
